get an off_t pointer: lseek(filed, 0, SEEK_CUR)
set an off_t pointer: lseek(filed, n, SEEK_SET)
rewind: lseek(fild, 0, SEEK_SET)
append (but why?) : lseek(filed, 1, SEEK_END);

since data is not garbage collected, copy-on-write must be used

seperate files for each party and each room
parties are named for the uuid of the party leader
rooms are named for the room ID

entire file is a .tar.bz2

individual files are .dat.gz
